
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sreekantiah-idr-segment-routing-te-00.txt'>
    <title>"Segment Routing Traffic Engineering Policy using BGP", Arjun Sreekantiah, Clarence Filsfils, Stefano Previdi, Siva Sivabalan, Paul Mattes, Jerome Marcon</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sreekantiah-idr-segment-routing-te-00.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes mechanisms allowing advertising Segment Routing Traffic Engineering (SRTE) policies using BGP.  Through the mechanisms described in this document, a BGP speaker has the ability to trigger, in a remote BGP node, the setup of a SR Encapsulation policy with specific characteristics and an explicit path.  Steering mechanisms are also defined to enable the application of the policy on a per BGP route basis.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-10-16T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
